erson   is far more common than its Russian equivalent, <b>Andreev</b>. The personal name was popular throughout Europe in various vernacular forms (including Italian <i>Andrea</i>, French <i>André</i>, Spanish <i>Andrés</i>, Scottish, North German, and Scandinavian <i>Anders</i>, Dutch <i>Andries</i>, Hungarian <i>András</i>, Czech <i>Ondřej</i>, Polish <i>Andrzej</i> and <i>Jędrzej</i>, and Russian <i>Andrey</i>).","Americanized or Germanized form of Slovenian <b>Andrejaš</b>: from an old vernacular form of the personal name <i>Andraž</i> (from Latin <i>Andreas</i>), which is a variant of <i>Andrej</i>; see   Andrew  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"d’Andria was born in 1240, in Andria, Bari, Puglia, Italy. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs. Margarita De Andria."},"et":{"1240–":"1240–Surnud","1245–Female":"1245–Surnud","1256–1291":"1256–1291","1240–Male":"1240–Surnud","Abt 1256":"umbes 1256","1256":"1256","1245":"1245","1240":"1240","1291":"1291","Andria, Bari, Apulia, Italy":"Andria, Bari, Puglia, Itaalia","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1240–":"1240–Kuollut","1245–Female":"1245–Kuollut","1256–1291":"1256–1291","1240–Male":"1240–Kuollut","Abt 1256":"noin 1256","1256":"1256","1245":"1245","1240":"1240","1291":"1291","Andria, Bari, Apulia, Italy":"Andria, Bari, Puglia, Italia","France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"1240–":"1240–Décédé","1245–Female":"1245–Décédée","1256–1291":"1256–1291","1240–Male":"1240–Décédé","Abt 1256":"environ 1256","1256":"1256","1245":"1245","1240":"1240","1291":"1291","Andria, Bari, Apulia, Italy":"Andria, Bari, Puglia, Italie","France":"France","lifeSummary":"d’Andria est né en 1240, à Andria, Bari, Puglia, Italie. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Mrs. Margarita De Andria."},"de":{"1240–":"1240–Verstorben","1245–Female":"1245–Verstorben","1256–1291":"1256–1291","1240–Male":"1240–Verstorben","Abt 1256":"um 1256","1256":"1256","1245":"1245","1240":"1240","1291":"1291","Andria, Bari, Apulia, Italy":"Andria, Bari, Puglia, Italien","France":"Frankreich","lifeSummary":